1936;;Pot Luck;;British;;Tom Walls;;Ralph Lynn, Robertson Hare;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pot_Luck_(1936_film);;A retired Scotland Yard detective, Patrick Fitzpatrick (Tom Walls) comes back to take one final case, tracking down a missing vase which has been stolen by a gang of thieves specialising in taking art treasures. His investigation takes him to the home of the innocent Mr Pye (Robertson Hare), whose house has been used by the crooks to hide their proceeds.[2][3]